🚨 Biggest Mistakes Engineers Make
❌ Mistake 1: Editing configuration without restarting or reloading

If you modify a service's configuration, the running service usually won't use it until you reload or restart it.

❌ Mistake 2: Forgetting daemon-reload

After changing or creating a service file under /etc/systemd/system/, always run:

sudo systemctl daemon-reload

Otherwise, systemd won't recognize your changes.

❌ Mistake 3: Enabling a service before verifying it works

First:

Start the service.
Check its status.
Review logs if needed.
Then enable it to start automatically on boot.
